values: 倒；灌；斟（饮料）；涌流；倾泻；倾诉；大量涌出；流淌；倒满；灌输；喷发；不断涌向（或涌现）；使（液体）连续流出；倾斜倒出；迅速移动；
倾泻；涌流；流出；大量流出；大雨；倾盆大雨；（已熔金属的）一次浇注量

word_mean_info__list.difference: 指水或其它液体从源头流出，不断地朝某一方向流动，可用作引申。
通常指从高向低或从上向下的急剧流动。也可作引申用。
侧重水继续不断地往前流，不关心其流量的大小和速度的快慢。
指液体向任何方向流动，暗示比flow快而有力。

word_group.phrase: it never rains but it pours

word_group.brief_definition: 对…持批评（或不支持）态度；对…泼冷水

bilingual.source: She pulled out the bung to pour the liquid.
The liquid is flowable and easy to pour.
bilingual.target: 这种液体是可流动的，很容易倒出。

bilingual.source: The syrup is too thick to pour easily.
bilingual.target: 这个糖浆太浓了，不容易倒出来。

bilingual.source: This syrup is very sticky and hard to pour out.
bilingual.target: 这个糖浆非常黏稠，很难倒出来。

bilingual.source: The viscidity of honey makes it difficult to pour.
bilingual.target: 蜂蜜的黏性使得它很难倒出来。

bilingual.source: The stickiness of this syrup makes it hard to pour.
bilingual.target: 这个糖浆的粘性让它很难倒出来。

bilingual.source: The honey was so viscous that it took a long time to pour.
bilingual.target: 蜂蜜非常粘稠，倒出来花了很长时间。

bilingual.source: The viscosity of this liquid is very high, making it hard to pour.
bilingual.target: 这液体的黏性很高，很难倒出来。
把水倒出来简直易如反掌。

list.abstract: pour（英 [pɔː]，美 [pɔːr]），英语单词，作动词为涌流；倾诉；纷至沓来。例句：Pour out his frustrations on a rate-your-employer website.（在一个评价雇主的网站上倾诉他的挫折。）短语搭配有pour into（倒入，倒进）。 近义词有issue、flux。

yingyinNormal.en: So you tamp, pack, turn the knob, wait 3, blast for 30, then you pour the shot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你就塞，压，拧手把，等3秒烧30秒再倒出咖啡。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, okay, then you let me go grocery shopping. No problem. I'm not done yet. And I buy laundry detergent, but it's not the one with the easy-pour spout.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你让我去买日常用品，我买了洗衣粉。没问题。我还没说完，但是是不容易倒出来的那种。

yingyinNormal.en: Finally, the beer. No drinking, just pour, just pour some of the beer over the fish.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最后加入啤酒。不许喝，全倒进去！把部分啤酒浇在鱼身上。

yingyinNormal.en: So just pour in, give that a good stir. Quick taste.
yingyinNormal.zh: 倒进去，充分搅拌。尝一下。

yingyinNormal.en: You can even join a cruise to see the lava pour into the ocean.
yingyinNormal.zh: 您甚至可以乘搭游船观看熔岩涌入大海。

yingyinNormal.en: You'll be in a very junior seat. Il faut reculer pour mieux sauter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 您会做次席的。要跳得远，得退一步。

yingyinNormal.en: Then finally pour over the meat juices, which will soak into the bread.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然后把肉汁浇上，会吃到面包里。

yingyinNormal.en: Days later, you're walking in the park when suddenly it starts to pour rain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 几天之后，你在公园散步突然下了一场大雨。

yingyinNormal.en: Millions pour to the capital from all over the country every year to seek their fortune.
yingyinNormal.zh: 数百万的人从全国各地涌入首都北京，年年来寻找他们的财富。

yingyinNormal.en: See, I actually can pour milk, but I got you believing that I couldn't. Now, see, that's acting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我会倒牛奶，我把你骗倒了，这就是演技。

yingyinNormal.en: That infomercial. For the milk carton spout thing. You're the guy that doesn't know how to pour milk.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那支公益广告，倒盒装牛奶那一支，你是那个不会倒牛奶的人。

yingyinNormal.en: Hmm, he's not crazy about needles, but if you get him to go jogging, it'll just pour out of his nose.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他不喜欢针头，但你要是让他去跑步他的鼻子就会自动喷血了。

yingyinNormal.en: If you didn't pour the coffee, no one would have anything to drink. Believe me, sometimes that happens.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没有你来倒咖啡呢，大家都休想喝到东西了。相信我，有时候真的会这样的。

yingyinNormal.en: We simply pour the oil into the engine and oh… What's wrong? There's nothing in here. The engine's gone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们只要把这桶汽油倒到油箱里，然后，噢。怎么了？这里面什么也没有，引擎消失了。

yingyinNormal.en: What'd you do, Romeo? You pour maple syrup all over your body and ask her if she was in the mood for a short stack?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你干啥了，罗密欧？往身上倒枫蜜，问她有没有性致玩3P？

yingyinNormal.en: Then all we do now is let the flavors of the stock and the mushrooms infuse with the meatballs. So just pour them into the dish.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然后我们要让汤和蘑菇的味道浸入到肉丸中，把汁浇在肉丸上。

yingyinNormal.en: People who go through things for you, people who pour their heart and souls into their jobs because they care should be valued and embraced.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为在乎你们而为你们做事的人，为工作呕心沥血的人，应该得到珍惜，得到拥抱。

yingyinNormal.en: We'll fire up some steaks, we'll pour a little wine, you pop into those short shorts, I chase you around the living room, that type of thing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们把牛排一烤，美酒一倒，你把那条短裤一穿，我在客厅和你追逐打闹，就那事儿，你懂的。

yingyinNormal.en: Fresh vegetable stock. This is a good cheat, or you can use you know the cubed vegetable stock. You can get these in the supermarket, just pour that on top.
yingyinNormal.zh: 新鲜蔬菜汤料。偷懒的好方法，你也可以用块状的，能在超市买到，浇在上面。

yingyinNormal.en: If you pat and pour into the middle, what's happening now is because you're giving it some aggression, the moisture from those sultanas are beginning to release.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你往中间拍打揉面，就像现在一样，因为你给它一些击打，葡萄干中的水分就开始挥发出来。

数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

sense_info_list.en: express one's feelings or thoughts in a full and unrestrained way

examination_example.sentence: Imagine you are <highlight>pouring</highlight> your heart out to someone and they are just busy on their phone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 想象一下，你正在向某人倾吐心声，而他们正忙着打电话。

sense_info_list.en: flow rapidly in a steady stream, especially of a liquid
sense_info_list.zh: 倒出; 倾泻; 喷发

sense_info_list.en: donate something to a particular enterprise or project in large amounts, especially money
(of people or things) come or go in a steady stream and in large numbers

word_usage.usage: pour作动词时，既可作及物动词，又可作不及物动词。作及物动词时，其后可接名词或代词，如：pour a glass of water
表示“给某人倒某物”时，可用pour sb. sth.表达，也可以用介词for来表达：pour sth. for sb.

sense_info_list.en: flow rapidly in a steady stream, especially of a liquid

examination_example.sentence: For the next nine days, until the well was capped, the well <highlight>poured</highlight> out more oil than all the wells in America combined.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在接下来的九天里，在油井封顶之前，油井流出的石油甚至超过了美国所有油井的总和。

examination_example.sentence: Experts also need to assess damage from the vast quantities of water firefighters <highlight>poured</highlight> into the cathedral.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 专家还需要评估消防员涌入大教堂的大量积水造成的损害。

sense_info_list.en: donate something to a particular enterprise or project in large amounts, especially money

examination_example.sentence: The dream of personalised flight is still vivid in the minds of many inventors, some developing cycle-powered craft, others <highlight>pouring</highlight> money into jet packs (喷气飞行背包).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 个性化飞行的梦想在许多发明家的脑海中仍然历历在目，一些人正在开发循环动力飞行器，另一些人则在喷气飞行背包中投入大量资金。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 去一个给老板打分的网站上将他的沮丧一吐为快。

examination_example.sentence: We'll <highlight>pour</highlight> about 30 percent more liquid into a short, wide glass than a tall, skinny glass.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们在一个又矮又宽的杯子里倒的液体要比在一个又高又细的杯子里多30%。

examination_example.sentence: By the time the group got up to leave, it was <highlight>pouring</highlight> outside.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当这群人起身准备离开时，外面正下着倾盆大雨。

examination_example.sentence: People have been <highlight>pouring</highlight> into stadiums since the days of ancient Greece.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从古希腊时代起，人们就已大量涌入体育场。
